N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 20, ch. IV, subch. A, pt. 560 - Repealed

State Regulations

Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 20, ch. IV, subch. A, pt. 560

By order filed April 16, 1987, Part 560 is repealed, effective April 8, 1991; provided, however, that such repeal shall not affect
or impair any act done or suffered, right accruing, accrued or acquired, or
liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred prior to such repeal, but
the same may be enjoyed, asserted, enforced, prosecuted or inflicted, as fully
and to the same extent as if such repeal had not been effected. All actions and
proceedings, civil or criminal, commenced under or by virtue of such Part 560
and pending immediately prior to the fourth anniversary of the date of
termination following in 1991, or commenced thereafter may be presented and
defended to final effect in the same manner as they might if such Part 560 was
not so repealed. State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
